    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT-6613 SERIES - AIR SYSTEM -
        SLAVE VALVE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>SLAVE VALVE</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1303010">Figure 10</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1303010" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1303010" filename="../figg13/g1303010.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 10. Slave Valve</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The slave valve assembly uses a poppet valve construction which reduces O-ring sealing problems and is
            extremely tolerant to contamination and moisture in the air system. Should this unit prove to be defective,
            replace the complete slave valve assembly, as it is a non-serviceable item. Failure to use the correct
            spring, plunger pin, and hat-type sleeve when installing the valve assembly will cause hard shifting in low
            range gears.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
